main event: Major C.A. Bauer and Cpt E.J. Jenson observed a brownish-yellowish unidentified object in the sky at McMurdo Station on 22 January 1963.
interesting points: The object appeared and disappeared at intervals and was not clearly defined., The object displayed a succession of shape and color changes., It was suspected to be related to atmospheric conditions but did not resemble known aerial phenomena., A second observation was made by Commander Moore and multiple personnel., The object was observed for a total of 4 minutes during routine duties.
witness description: Major C.A. Bauer and Cpt E.J. Jenson
